The Hammer of Light has decimated the Vasudan fleet at Vega.  Most of the surviving Vasudan forces have retreated to Deneb and Antares.  Because our fleet is also holding Antares, relations between the VPE and the GTA have been strained.

In order to quell the tension, we have been ordered to eliminate all Hammer of Light outposts in the vicinity.  Fortunately, we have some new tools to assist us."

2331, "$b New $b Technology: $b Phoenix $b V $b Missile

Our first new weapon is the Phoenix V anti-bomber warhead.  This missile can puncture even the thickest of shields, and can also be used effectively against larger targets, like freighters.  More details are available in the Tech Room."

2332, "$b New $b Technology: $b Medusa $b Bomber

We have also acquired a wing of the new Medusa bombers.  Though they are slower and less maneuverable than the Athena, they are far more powerful.  Once again, full details can be found in the Tech Room."

2333, "$b New $b Technology: $b Tsunami $b Space $b Bomb

The new Tsunami bomb is the ultimate anti-cruiser weapon, and can be carried by the Medusas.  Just a few of these will take out any cruiser, and the Hammer of Light Aten-class cruisers are no exception.  You'll be using this bomb quite often against major Hammer of Light outposts."

